.<br>
<br>
I have asked my guild to assist me to go one step further.  I will take a lesser character that has no taken any Scale or CoV faction hits to record the static mobs positions and any wanderers within the zone.  I will try and locate good camping positions and the best route to the exit.<br>
<br>
With this information it may be possible to plot a raid into this zone with the backing of a passive group.<br>
<br>
I would also imagine that a raid in this zone will hurt a lot though. <p>Sheiba Darkheart<BR>
Lvl 57 Rogue<BR>
Server - Brell Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 516<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/5/01 10:24:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ToV</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I will take a lesser character that has no taken any Scale or CoV faction hits to record the static mobs positions and any wanderers within the zone. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Was told this weekend that ToV is a 46+ zone same as the planes.  So it can't be too lesser of a character. Also I believe that you start out KoS to CoV faction.  My shaman is on giant faction so never got any hits either way on CoV and he's KoS in Skyshrine. <p>Twiggie Tymberwolf
